Description: Fragment of rim of Attic black-figured pottery open vase, probably a type A or proto-A cup. Interior and top of lip glazed; band near lip on outside; below, part of large female head facing left.
Curator's comments: This would appear to be a large head on the lip of a proto-A cup or the like, but without a photo of the inside one cannot press the case.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.2196)
